(147, 1, '2016-09-29 02:39:01', '2016-09-29 02:39:01', 'Rory McIlroy PGA Tour is a shallow, lifeless golf game--rich in technical failings but bankrupt of interesting content. The game types are limited, the number of players and courses is laughably small, and the textures awkwardly pop in and out of view as the camera scrolls across a course. Actually swinging a club and mapping out shots feels right, but whatever goodwill is earned on the course evaporates as you pull away to discover the unimpressive Pro Career mode and the restrictive nature of even the basic Play Now feature. The fresh face on the cover and fancy new game engine can''t mask the fact that Rory McIlroy PGA Tour is an undercooked debut that feels like half of a game.\\\r\n[arve url="https://youtu.be/5eQKOr6sFgk"]', 'Rory Mcilroy PGA Tour', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'rory-mcilroy-pga-tour', '', '', '2016-09-29 02:43:34', '2016-09-29 02:43:34', '', 0, 'http://www.ajaysworld.com/teamdragon/?p=147', 0, 'post', '', 0),
